description:
come build at the intersection of ai and fintech. at ocrolus, we’re on a mission to help lenders automate workflows with confidence—streamlining how financial institutions evaluate borrowers and enabling faster, more accurate lending decisions.



our ai workflow and analytics platform for lenders is trusted at scale, processing nearly one million credit applications every month across small business, mortgage, and consumer lending. by integrating state\-of\-the\-art open\- and closed\-source ai models with our human\-in\-the\-loop verification engine, ocrolus captures data from financial documents with over 99% accuracy. thanks to our advanced fraud detection and comprehensive cash flow and income analytics, our customers achieve greater efficiency in risk management, and provide expanded access to credit—ultimately creating a more inclusive financial system.



trusted by more than 400 customers—including industry leaders like better mortgage, brex, enova, nova credit, paypal, plaid, sofi, and square—ocrolus stands at the forefront of ai innovation in fintech. join us, and help redefine how the world’s most innovative lenders do business.



senior machine learning engineer (ocrolus inc.; new york, ny): work with the product and operations teams to understand the business, and the different problem spaces at play. lead initiatives to identify high\-impact areas where machine learning (ml) can provide significant value and competitive advantage. coordinate with operations to define data collection needs, and prescribe collection methodology ensuring quality. architect, deploy, test, maintain and improve on existing state\-of\-the\-art ml models and infrastructure ensuring scalability and robustness. identify areas and implement advanced techniques, such as ensemble methods, for continuous improvement (performance and accuracy) of the ml models. develop tooling such as analytical frameworks to enable continuous performance evaluation and alerting systems to ensure model reliability. lead research initiatives to explore and evaluate proof of concepts (pocs) for innovative ml solutions, focusing on automation of internal tasks. apply expert software engineering skills and integrate successful pocs into the system ensuring efficient, clean and maintainable code, adhering to industry standard best practices. mentor junior engineers in the process. design scalable solutions that employ modern, state\-of\-the\-art ml and deep learning techniques for the purpose of performing image classification, image localization and segmentation, and natural language processing. use frontend technologies, to build lightweight user interface (ui) components for better interaction with ml systems. optimize ml model training by effectively leveraging gpus and linux systems. ensure efficient resource management and performance tuning for faster model training. understand the entire system end to end, learning new technologies related to site reliability, such as docker and kubernetes. gain a holistic view of the infrastructure to quickly identify and solve issues. stay up\-to\-date with the latest advancements in ml and related fields, continuously doing research and updating skills and knowledge.



telecommuting permitted from anywhere in the u.s.


**minimum requirements**: master’s degree or foreign equivalent in engineering, computer science, robotics, or a related field.



must have experience with the following:



1\. python, go and sql;  

2\. java and javascript;  

3\. machine learning framework: keras, tensorflow and pytorch;  

4\. machine learning operations technologies: docker, helm, kubernetes;  

5\. cloud infrastructure: aws, gcp, azure;  

6\. data manipulation libraries: numpy, pandas, scikit\-learn;  

7\. design and improvement of large\-scale distributed production environments;  

8\. version control, git, rest, unit, integration, and regression testing;  

9\. mathematics: linear algebra, probability theory, statistics, calculus and algorithms;  

10\. data modeling and pipelining: feeding datasets into model training efficiently;  

11\. model evaluation in production: leverage labeled data to provide feedback and analysis of performance;  

and  

12\. auc precision recall metrics.



skills may be gained through academic coursework and concurrently while pursuing academic studies.



to apply: any interested applicant may click on the apply now button above to apply for this position.



email: pwahby@ocrolus.com



**life at ocrolus**



we’re a team of builders, thinkers, and problem solvers who care deeply about our mission — and each other. as a fast\-growing, remote\-first company, we offer an environment where you can grow your skills, take ownership of your work, and make a meaningful impact.


**our culture is grounded in four core values:**  

**empathy –** understand and serve with compassion  

**curiosity –** explore new ideas and question the status quo  

**humility –** listen, be grounded, and remain open\-minded  

**ownership –** love what you do, work hard, and deliver excellence



we believe diverse perspectives drive better outcomes. that’s why we’re committed to fostering an inclusive workplace where everyone has a seat at the table, regardless of race, gender, gender identity, age, disability, national origin, or any other protected characteristic.



we look forward to building the future of lending together.
